and that's it so far, thanks for reading. i'm excited to keep creating and sharing my journey with you all. 

I hope this thread can inspire more artists to join this space and find creative freedom.

if you want, you can check out my genesis here: https://t.co/mAO3jzZoxK

âœŒï¸

9/
what i find really awesome is, out of the 14 people who bought one of my nfts, only 2 were people i know irl. the other 12 I met on discord and twitter just from being in the mix. one of my favorite things about this space is that people genuinely like to support artists.

8/
while it isn't all about the money for me, it's a nice feeling to finally be rewarded for your creativity and see that it's possible to make a living off your art. esp after years of companies pricing your song at $1 and paying crumbs for thousands of people listening to it.

7/
this showed me a smaller group of supporters in web3 can be more powerful than a large traditional fanbase. the equivalent of almost half a million streams came from just 14 people...wtf

6/
to put this into perspective, to make $1800 from streaming, you would need ~450,000 streams on sp*tify. if the 14 people who collected my genesis wanted to support me in the same way they did when they bought my nft, theyâ€™d each need to stream my song 32,000 timesâ€¦

5/
fast forward, i dropped my genesis nft project on jan 19th, 2022. 26 nfts, each one featuring my new song "Make Sure" and a unique artwork, priced at 0.05ETH ~$130 

out of 26, so far i've sold 14 for a total of 0.7ETH. after OS fees i saw 0.68ETH which is around ~$1800 rn

4/
in the months that followed, i spent all my free time researching and learning everything i possibly could.

I minted and bought a bunch of nfts, ventured into defi, got rugged, got rekt, fumbled some bags but learned 
a lot (21 voice) and also made some awesome new frens.

3/
after feeling stuck for awhile, I discovered nfts and i took the deep dive this past summer. immediately it felt like everything i had been looking for. a place that offers creative freedom and the ability to value my art as i see fit.
